OL,3,CDomestic abuse charity calls for more
OL,4,Csupport saying system is 'broken'
OL,6,FThe charity also runs voluntary
OL,7,Fprogrammes for perpetrators of
OL,8,Fdomestic abuse and sexual violence to
OL,9,Fhelp them change their behaviour.
OL,11,F"Many of those people do want to
OL,12,Fchange their behaviour," Ms Marshall
OL,13,Fexplained. "And perhaps have been
OL,14,Fabused themselves or have been
OL,15,Findoctrinated in toxic relationships
OL,16,Fthemselves."
OL,18,F"It's very difficult work and not many
OL,19,Fstep forward, but when they do they
OL,20,Fcan change their lives forever," she
OL,21,Fadded.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
